Web Server (IIS) in Windows Server
Definition

A Web Server hosts websites and delivers web pages to users using:

HTTP

HTTPS

In Windows Server, the web server service is called IIS (Internet Information Services).

Requirement

Windows Server installed

Static IP configured

Logged in as Administrator

DNS Server (optional but recommended)

Example Used
Server Name: WEB01
Website Folder: C:\WebSite
Port: 80
URL: http://server1.company.local

PART 1: Install IIS Web Server Role
Step 1: Open Server Manager

Login to Windows Server

Open Server Manager

Step 2: Add Roles and Features

Click Manage

Select Add Roles and Features

Click Next

Select Role-based or feature-based installation

Click Next

Select Local Server

Click Next

Step 3: Select Web Server (IIS)

Select Web Server (IIS)

Click Add Features

Click Next

Click Next

Click Install

Step 4: Installation Complete

IIS Web Server is now installed

PART 2: Verify IIS Installation
Step 1: Open Browser

Open web browser on server

Enter:

http://localhost

Verification

IIS Default Page is displayed

Web Server is working

PART 3: Create Website Folder
Step 1: Create Folder

Create folder:

C:\WebSite

Step 2: Create HTML File

Open Notepad

Add:

<html>
<body>
<h1>Welcome to IIS Web Server</h1>
</body>
</html>


Save as:

index.html


Save location:

C:\WebSite

PART 4: Set NTFS Permissions
Step 1: Configure Permissions

Right-click C:\WebSite

Click Properties

Open Security tab

Click Edit

Add:

IIS_IUSRS


Allow:

Read

Read & Execute

Click Apply

Click OK

PART 5: Create New Website in IIS
Step 1: Open IIS Manager

Open Server Manager

Click Tools

Select Internet Information Services (IIS) Manager

Step 2: Add Website

Right-click Sites

Click Add Website

Step 3: Website Details
Site Name: CompanySite
Physical Path: C:\WebSite
Binding Type: http
IP Address: All Unassigned
Port: 80
Host Name: server1.company.local


Click OK

PART 6: Configure DNS (Optional)
Create DNS A Record
Name: server1
IP Address: 192.168.1.10

PART 7: Access Website from Client
From Client Browser
http://server1.company.local


or

http://192.168.1.10

Verification

Website loads successfully

HTML page is displayed

Common IIS Commands
iisreset

Conclusion

IIS Web Server has been successfully installed and configured in Windows Server.
The server is now hosting a website and accessible from client machines.
